The user is asking if the code they're currently using is based on load_data.py as a reference. Let me compare both scripts.

Looking at load_data.py:

Uses mne.io.read_raw_brainvision() to read EEG files

Uses raw.annotations to get annotations

Uses mne.events_from_annotations(raw) to get events

Creates DataFrames with pd.DataFrame()

Extracts time, label, event counts

Has sections: RAW INFO, ANNOTATIONS, ANNOTATION COUNTS, EVENT ID, FIRST 30 EVENTS, EVENT COUNTS, SUMMARY

Now looking at extract_september_simple.py, it's using the exact same approach—same MNE functions, same DataFrame construction, same section headers and data extraction patterns. The code is clearly modeled after load_data.py, just adapted to handle batch processing across multiple files.

是的，extract_september_simple.py 完全是以 load_data.py 为参考写的。两者结构对比：

部分	load_data.py	extract_september_simple.py
读取EEG	mne.io.read_raw_brainvision()	完全一样 ✓
Annotations	raw.annotations	完全一样 ✓
Events	mne.events_from_annotations(raw)	完全一样 ✓
DataFrame	pd.DataFrame(sample, event_code)	完全一样 ✓
章节标题	RAW INFO, ANNOTATIONS, EVENT ID...	完全一样 ✓
输出	print()	改为写入文件 (主要区别)
唯一的区别是：

load_data.py → 针对单个文件，直接print输出到控制台
extract_september_simple.py → 批量处理5个文件，输出保存为 *_output.txt
所以回答是：是的，我们的提取脚本是以 load_data.py 为模板/参考写的，核心逻辑完全相同。

